analysts estimated at $ 10.84 according to the FactSet 's review .
the decline in the forecast comes despite a rise in rates averaging 4.9 per cent , which will come into effect on January 4 , and the growth of fees for land transportation of heavy or overall cargo , which begins in November .
the company said it was still planning an increase in revenue compared to last year thanks to spending cuts , increased gross revenue and the growth of online trading .
chairman and CEO Fred Smith said the company had `` worked steadily on account of the weak , compared to the forecast , economic conditions , especially in manufacturing and world trade . ''
Labour 's hiring plans for the holidays were announced the following day after the competitor 's statement , UPS , of plans to hire an extra 95 000 staff , roughly as much as they took to work last year .
for the quarter , which ended August 31 , FedEx earned $ 692 million , a 6 percent increase from the year before .
earnings per share were $ 2.42 , close to the forecast at an average of $ 2.44 a share held by Zacks Investment Research overturned 12 analysts .
revenue increased by 5 % , to $ 12.3 billion .
six analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $ 12.23 billion .
