for several years , bariatric surgery has proven to be effective for the treatment of type 2 diabetes , but basic research was conducted among people with morphine obesity having the body mass index ( IMT ) 35 or higher .
IMT , a measure of weight relative to growth , is considered normal at value from 18.5 to 24.9 .
IMT 25 or above suggests that a person is overweight and people with IMT above 30 are considered people with obesity .
you can calculate your IMT here : 1.usa.gov/1D0ZqDv .
for the new study , researchers from Min-Sheng General 's Taiwan hospital have used data collected since 2007 to compare two types of bariatric surgery - Shuning of stomach and elongated gastocomia , with a medical treatment of 2 diabetes patients with little obesity .
the average value of IMT among those undergoing surgery has fallen from 31 to 24.5 by the end of the fifth year of their involvement in the study .
at the same time the BMI of those who received non-surgical treatment from diabetes remains at about 29 .
among those who suffered the surgery fully cured of diabetes by 36 % , and partially - 28 % .
in a group receiving drug treatment , for comparison , the total cure for diabetes was only 1 % , and a partial one - only about 2 % .
in addition , blood pressure levels , triglycerides and `` bad '' LPNP cholesterol were `` generally better in the surgical group , '' the authors claim .
the researchers also monitored the levels of haemoglobin blood cells that reflect levels of sugar in the blood in the dynamics .
hemoglobin A1c better hold below 7 % , '' the researchers write .
after surgery the average level of hemoglobin A1c reduced from about 9 % to about 6 % .
in a therapeutic group , however , it remained stable , about 8 % .
but the best indicators of glycemic control , reflected in good levels of hemoglobin A1c , have not reduced the death rate in five years , according to the head of research by Dr. Chi-Cheng Su and colleagues .
the research team also compared the average outcomes of two types of surgical treatment .
for the fifth year , in comparison with the band polled by a sleeveless touring band , the shuncing group lost more weight ( 18.7 kg against 14.2 kg ) , achieved a larger reduction of IMT ( at 7.4 vs. 5.1 ) and hemoglobin versus ( 3.1 % vs. 2.1 % ) , and was closer to the full remission of diabetes ( 46.9 % vs. 16.7 % ) .
although the new study does not show the benefits of the surgical method in part of life expectancy after five years , there are confirmation of the results of a study of patients with an overweight body in Sweden that surgical treatment actually leads to an increase in life expectancy , as reported by Blexstone from the College of Medicine in Phoenix , the University of Arizona .
according to a Swedish study for people with obesity , who pushed the bariatric intervention , the chance to die for 15 years was about 29 % lower compared to the group in which more traditional methods were applied .
