Xi Jinping calls to make economy more open to peace
the economy should become more open to the whole world to spur its growth , as President Xi Jinping said on Tuesday in an address to the group ahead of the challenge to the reform guide .
`` China should concentrate on attracting foreign investors and experts and developing a policy of openness , '' he said , addressing the participants of the 16th meeting of the Central Front Committee for comprehensive deepening of reforms .
he said that increasing openness and deepening reforms would give the economy a new impetus and vitality and provide a new space for economic development .
the leading group has adopted a number of directives , including introducing the regulation of investor access to the market , changing border controls , the encouragement of state-owned enterprises ( SOE ) , attracting private capital and revising the registration system for residents .
according to the statement , a list of sectors of economy and production , inaccessible to investment , will be drawn up .
the system will be gradually worked out through trial programs .
this is an important step , as it will give the market a more significant role in the allocation of resources , ensuring legitimacy in business and increased openness , as the statement said .
the government will also weaken control of the powers given to them by firms , ensuring that companies themselves will run their business .
the statement also said that China would allow border regions to master new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to boost local growth .
more areas will be made available to private investors in order to improve the openness of the state-controlled sectors of the economy .
`` The government will not change its policy towards foreign investors and will protect the legitimate interests of companies with foreign financing , and provide them with better conditions , '' the statement said .
in addition there will be a simplified procedure for applying for permanent residence permit , or `` grin-card , '' by optimizing requirements and simplifying the process of the application process .
the meeting also discussed the protection of lawyers ' rights and questions of training of professional judges and prosecutor 's office .
according to the official report released after the meeting , Prime Minister Li Keqiang and ministers Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli were also present .
